      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions are fully characterized and replicated in the CFD boundary conditions. Flow rates measured with Coriolis mass flowmeter (±0.5% FS), rotational speed with optical tachometer (±5 RPM), fluid viscosity measured at test temperature with cone-plate rheometer (±2%), and hematocrit confirmed by microhematocrit centrifugation. All five operating points are within the defined operating envelope. Test fluid (porcine blood, hematocrit 38±1%) is representative of clinical VAD operating conditions. Temperature controlled to 37±0.5°C throughout testing.",
