      "rationale": "Model form selection justified through systematic comparison of four turbulence model variants (k-ω SST, realizable k-ε, RSM, LES) against PIV data at two operating points. k-ω SST selected based on superior velocity field agreement (MAE 4.2% vs 6.8–11.3% for alternatives) and computational tractability. Hemolysis model form (Giersiepen-Wurzinger power law) selected based on published calibration against RBC lysis data; model form uncertainty quantified via comparison with Zhang power-law variant (±8% NIH). Lagrangian particle tracking confirmed representative with 50,000 particles per operating point (convergence study: <1% NIH change beyond 30,000 particles). Model form uncertainty included in total uncertainty budget.",
