      "rationale": "All model input parameters characterized with quantified uncertainties: fluid viscosity (±2%, measured), density (±0.5%, literature), hemolysis power-law coefficients C, α, β (±15%, ±8%, ±12% respectively, from Giersiepen et al. calibration dataset with bootstrap uncertainty), pump geometry (±0.1 mm, CMM measurement), rotational speed (±5 RPM, tachometer). Global sensitivity analysis (Sobol indices, N=10,000) identifies β and Cμ as dominant contributors. Targeted experimental recalibration of β reduced its uncertainty from ±12% to ±6%. Full input uncertainty propagation performed via Monte Carlo, yielding 95% CI on NIH of ±14% relative.",
